HEADWORD: Lithotomist
<hw>Li*thot"o*mist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>lithotomiste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who performs the operation of
cutting for stone in the bladder, or one who is skilled in the
operation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

